**Description:** **: This code defines a class named Tools that serves as a wrapper for interacting with the Wayback Machine API. It includes a nested Pydantic model (Valves) for configuration settings like API base URL and user agent. The class has an initializer to set up these configurations and two main methods: `get_archived_snapshot`, which retrieves the closest archived snapshot of a specified URL (optionally based on a timestamp), and `get_capture_history`, which fetches the capture history of a URL from the Wayback CDX Server. The code handles API requests, error handling, and returns structured responses, making it a utility for web archiving and historical data retrieval.  

